GNUnix
======

This LICENSE applies to the build scripts, configuration, documentation,
and other infrastructure in this repository — the files that make up the
GNUnix distribution itself.

It does NOT apply to the upstream software that GNUnix builds and packages
(the Linux kernel, glibc, gcc, binutils, sysvinit, eudev, dbus, elogind,
GRUB, Nix, nixpkgs, sway, foot, and the rest of the userland). Each of
those retains its own upstream license (GPL, LGPL, BSD, MIT, MPL, Apache,
etc.) and is distributed under those terms.

The license below is the one used by Slackware Linux's build scripts. We
adopt it because the project philosophy is Slackware-adjacent (boring base,
no policy in PID 1, hand-curated `/etc/rc.d/`) and because it's the most
permissive form a copyright notice can take while still being a recognised
open-source license.

