A note on lineage
-----------------

The wording above is the canonical license header carried by every
SlackBuild script in the Slackware project. It is a one-clause BSD-style
permissive license — sometimes called the "Slackware build script license"
or "BSD-1-Clause" (SPDX: `BSD-1-Clause`). It is compatible with the GPL
and with the licenses of every package GNUnix builds.

A note on the produced images
-----------------------------

When GNUnix produces a Tart VM image, raw `.img.zst`, or hybrid `.iso`, the
resulting artifact is a *collection* of separately-licensed software, just
like any Linux distribution. Each binary in `/usr`, `/bin`, `/lib`, and
under `/nix/store` retains its upstream license. The license terms above
cover only the GNUnix-authored glue (rc.d scripts, build pipeline, Nix
expressions under `bundles/`, manifest, runbooks, ADRs, etc.) — not the
software the pipeline builds.

A note on contributions
-----------------------

By submitting a contribution (pull request, patch, issue, etc.) to this
repository, you agree that your contribution may be distributed under the
terms of this license. See `CONTRIBUTING.md` for the contribution process.
